N:agent-pulse
D:Operate and extend barretlee/agent-pulse as an evidence-backed AI industry intelligence system: source lifecycle, safe collection, signal normalization, Event clustering, system evaluation, Scout hypotheses, privacy-safe export, and release verification.
G:agent-pulse ai-intelligence evidence source-catalog collectors event-clustering scout github-pages industry-intelligence
U[8]:
  Run Agent Pulse locally and inspect its Control Room or public static site
  Add or audit a SourceAdapter with lifecycle, provenance, fixtures, and failure isolation
  Collect eligible signals, deduplicate and cluster Events, or audit source health
  Evaluate system capability and compare a baseline for regressions
  Generate bounded evidence-linked Scout opportunities
  Export and validate the privacy-safe public Pages site
  Change schemas, ranking, publication gates, or source lifecycle docs-first
  Report facts, evidence, judgments, uncertainty, and next signals separately
R[7]:
  Treat Agent Pulse as evidence-backed intelligence, not a news aggregator
  Aggregators are discovery or heat signals and never sole factual evidence
  Do not equate heat with factual confidence
  Do not bypass login, WAF, CAPTCHA, paywalls, robots, licenses, or rate limits
  Keep automatic Events in review until deterministic readiness gates pass
  Never export raw payloads, credentials, private operations, or database data to Pages
  Do not describe Scout hypotheses, seed data, or experimental features as facts or production capability
E[2]{desc,in,out}:
  "Add an official RSS source to Agent Pulse","SourceAdapter extension with fixtures, lifecycle gates, and npm run check","docs-first source change with safe adapter tests and audit-ready handoff"
  "Publish a hot Agent Pulse story from an aggregator","Evidence and readiness review before privacy-safe export","canonical original evidence, review status, and no aggregator-only publication"
